# Pin Python sources to LF line endings.
#
# Why: recurring CRLF-only diff noise on a small set of files
# (scripts/tools/context_views.py, trading_app/phase_4_discovery_gates.py,
#  trading_app/strategy_discovery.py, several test files) caused by
# autocrlf mismatch across machines/terminals.
#
# Scope is intentionally narrow (*.py only). Adding other text types
# risks rewriting files that have legitimately been committed with CRLF.
# Future text types should be added one at a time after verifying the
# current line-ending state across the tree.
#
# This file does NOT renormalize existing files. To apply LF to all .py
# in one sweep: `git add --renormalize "*.py" && git commit`. Coordinate
# across terminals first — that operation will collide with anyone
# holding CRLF dirty WIP.
#
# Origin: HANDOFF item O-CRLF, landed 2026-04-25.
*.py text eol=lf

# Pin specific hypothesis YAMLs to LF so SHA manifest (docs/audit/check_107_sha_migrations.yaml,
# enforced by check_drift.py Check 108) stays stable across platforms.
# Without this, Windows CI runners with default core.autocrlf=true check out these
# LF-indexed files as CRLF, producing a different SHA than the manifest records.
#
# Scope is intentionally per-file, NOT directory-wide: 65 sibling YAMLs in
# docs/audit/hypotheses/ are CRLF-committed and a broad `eol=lf` rule would
# silently renormalize them on the next checkout, breaking the same manifest
# for those files. Add per-file pins only for hypotheses recorded in the SHA
# manifest as LF.
# Origin: PR #298+#299 merge surfaced this via Check 108 (2026-05-17).
docs/audit/hypotheses/2026-05-11-llm-cme-preclose-atr-p30-o15.yaml   text eol=lf
docs/audit/hypotheses/2026-05-11-llm-cme-preclose-orb-vol-16k-o15.yaml text eol=lf
docs/audit/hypotheses/2026-05-11-llm-tokyo-open-atr-vel-ge105.yaml   text eol=lf
